<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101158676717260></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101158676717260><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=101158676717260>RE: Whats a Cleric to do?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=101158676717260#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122873><span id=Guru>Phreda the Hand</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>202 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jan 21st 12:20 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't know what level your cleric is, so maybe this wouldn't help at all....<br><br>Maybe you have a RL friend or relative who would like to join you for frequent playing?&nbsp;&nbsp;As a cleric, you are in a prime position to power level someone up to your level.  If you aren't too high up already, the power leveling wouldn't take very long.<br><br>My sister plays a cleric.  She called me up and convinced me to join the game as a tank.  We've been having a blast ever since!  We live 5000 miles apart, so the game is a marvelous way to hang out together.<br><br>And in a tank/cleric duo, she is never relegated to the back, just medding and healing.  We have to fight side by side to stay alive and get good mob XP.  I taunt constantly, so she can cast when she needs to, and melee when she doesn't.<br><br>Good luck friend!<br>&nbsp;<br>Phreda Biggles<br>34 Warrior, Drunken Bandit<br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=122873 target=_new>Tales of a Halfling Tank Girl</a></td></tr>
