<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101137309947926></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101137309947926><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=101137309947926>RE: Whats a Cleric to do?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=101137309947926#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=126045><span id= >Lunastaron</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 18th 11:58 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I can remember running into SK when I was camping gnolls and shouting for a group and not finding any.&nbsp;&nbsp;So I'd head over the to the undead ruins and kill skels for faction at Qeynos.  After about a half hour and no group, I'd get frustrated and head to the spires and look at the contents of some of the groups.  If there was a cleric free group (shaman or druid healing), I'd drop a heal and some cleric buffs on their MA, and sit and med nearby.  Several times I'd end up with an invite, or just a Breeze.<br><br>What Ancarett said is totally true; find a tank and duo.  You don't hafta wait for an invite.  And turn /LFG on, just so people who zone in afterward have a chance of seeing you.<br>&nbsp;<br>Lunastaron Solinar<br>Cleric of Tunare<br>E.Marr</td></tr>
